this is very hard to read and understand, and to maintain in the future
I would suggest to simplify it
maybe like this? ⬇️ 

```ts
type FindOptions<T, U> = {
    sort?: SortSpecifier;
    skip?: number;
    limit?: number;
    fields?: FieldSpecifier;
    reactive?: boolean;
    transform?: (doc: T) => U;
}
type FindOneOptions<T, U> = Omit<FindOptions<T, U>, "limit">;

find<Y = U>(selector?: Selector<T> | ObjectID | string, options?: FindOptions<T, Y>): Cursor<T, Y>
findOne<Y = U>(selector?: Selector<T> | ObjectID | string, options?: FindOneOptions<T, Y>): Cursor<T, Y>
```

I [tested](https://www.typescriptlang.org/play?#-CJwgQ4ikAB9QSp1FoBcZTp8AOaWOAwgEzT7Q--cdJxLDCUOwJNcKgABqKBG0bMj8PzQs0wzOcIm-X8lUA4DQPAx9K2XKCHgvXA4L1VZgCQ1D0PuSwtx3bd908fCqwIfBCFresIEbApyIAhBGxrTTjEbE9yCjVAAXPJwXFcCBGDXEwCIVLwX0sBxTnOS4EDaTwgJAuMwIgrjwh8AjnDcXwMWMlIDggFD6DgCUvDMtxLMCAAGYIUMk3d9x8aogA) and it seems TS is able to infer `Y` based on the transform function, so no need to explicitly define it

